    "name": [
      "Tim Bray on Blogging in 2017"
    ],
    "content": [
      {
        "html": "<p>Replied to <a class=\"u-in-reply-to\" href=\"https://www.tbray.org/ongoing/When/201x/2017/05/03/Blogging-in-2017\">a post on <strong>tbray.org</strong></a>:</p><p>Thank you, Tim, for still blogging, and owning your own identity on the web. Your presence makes it more vibrant, unique, and diverse.</p><blockquote><p>The great dan\u00adger is that the Web\u2019s fu\u00adture is mall-like: No space re\u00adal\u00adly pub\u00adlic, no store\u00adfronts but na\u00adtion\u00adal brands\u2019, no vi\u00adsu\u00adals com\u00adposed by am\u00ada\u00adteurs, noth\u00ading that\u2019s on of\u00adfer just for its own sake, and for love.</p></blockquote><p>This sentence in particular resonated with me. I want the web to be a massive, interconnected network of independant thinkers, businesses, artists, communicators, individuals, etc., not just a collection of brands shouting into the void, hoping to attract consumers.</p><p><a class=\"u-category\" href=\"https://news.indieweb.org/en\"></a><a class=\"p-category\" href=\"/tag/indienews\" rel=\"tag\">#indienews</a>\u00a0<a class=\"p-category\" href=\"/tag/indieweb\" rel=\"tag\">#indieweb</a> <a class=\"p-category\" href=\"/tag/micro\" rel=\"tag\">#micro</a></p>",
        "value": "Replied to a post on tbray.org:\nThank you, Tim, for still blogging, and owning your own identity on the web. Your presence makes it more vibrant, unique, and diverse.\nThe great dan\u00adger is that the Web\u2019s fu\u00adture is mall-like: No space re\u00adal\u00adly pub\u00adlic, no store\u00adfronts but na\u00adtion\u00adal brands\u2019, no vi\u00adsu\u00adals com\u00adposed by am\u00ada\u00adteurs, noth\u00ading that\u2019s on of\u00adfer just for its own sake, and for love.\nThis sentence in particular resonated with me. I want the web to be a massive, interconnected network of independant thinkers, businesses, artists, communicators, individuals, etc., not just a collection of brands shouting into the void, hoping to attract consumers.\n#indienews\u00a0#indieweb #micro"
      }
